#: 21337012-0-1607
msgctxt "21337012-0-1607"
msgid "Entry 271"
"\nCiryarel lived a long and blessed life, even for an Altmer, but no more. <<1>> believes she was killed by the Crosstree Bandits. ""A natural end to a life of skooma use,"" as she put it. Nonsense! My wife was no skooma fiend. Such aspersions slight her memory!"
"\n"
"\nRegardless of the Khajiit's assumptions, the Crosstrees are to blame. The evidence is overwhelming—broken phials scattered about the shore where she was found, the marks cut into her face—all of it points to the smugglers. Trinimac aid me, I will see her avenged!"
"\n"
"\nEntry 272"
"\nWaited by the docks for the better part of a week. Saw one of those fiends make a sale. Tried to follow him, but he saw me. Made a noise, two short whistles, one long. Must remember. Two of his friends jumped me from the rooftops. Beat me bloody. Tossed me off the dock."
"\n"
"\nAwoke as the tide washed the blood from my wounds. Still feel the sting. If I am to pursue these vermin—and vermin they are!—I must learn to defend myself."
"\n"
"\n<<2>> is a sturdy fellow and a fine friend. Years of dealing with surly drunks and ruffians have taught him many things, and he carries himself with a warrior's grace. Tomorrow I will ask him to teach me what he knows."
"\n"
"\nEntry 273"
"\n<<2>> could not stop laughing. He said I was like a kitten mewling for sweetcakes! When I explained myself and asked if he would teach me, his manner changed."
"\n"
"\nHe said, ""Go to the temple of <<3>>. Ask for <<4>>. Tell her what you told me."""
"\n"
"\nI leave tomorrow. I told <<5>> I'll be fishing the tidal pools near <<6>>. I think she believed me."
"\n"
"\nEntry 274"
"\n<<4>>'s story is not unlike my own. She lost a brother to the Crosstrees and came to <<6>>. She wanted to learn how to fight."
"\n"
"\nBut she says the monks are trained to think. Every martial lesson is a puzzle. Until students demonstrate their understanding, they cannot advance. Riddle'Thar gave her guidance and tempered her need for revenge with a desire for justice."
"\n"
"\nWhen she did act, it was calculated and precise. The Crosstrees never realized it was anything but an accident."
"\n"
"\nEntry 275"
"\nMy training proceeds well, though I have some difficulty with Riddle'Thar. It seems one must view one's self as a tiny part in a greater schema."
"\n"
"\nA novel way to think. Entirely different from the ways of old Aldmeris, though I admit it is far more flexible. Especially in regards to moral qualms. I will meditate upon this."
"\n"
"\nEntry 276"
"\nA calm settles about my thoughts. Sleep comes easily, where before it was elusive. Ciryarel's thread crosses mine in dreams where we watch our daughter spread wings and fly across the framework suspending us all."
"\n"
"\nAcross the void, the Crosstrees' thread glimmers like a dagger in the night. How easy it would be to sever their cord! To send them tumbling into the darkness beyond!"
"\n"
"\nBut imprecision is the greatest enemy. So I wait. I watch. And I learn."
"\n"
"\nEntry 277"
"\n<<4>> says the Crosstrees are vulnerable. Direct confrontation is out of the question. Better to sever those threads who stray from the rest, fraying the cord until it snaps."
"\n"
"\nThis one is ready."
msgstr ""
"항목 271"
"\n"
"시리아렐은 알트머라는 것을 감안해도 길고 축복받은 삶을 살았지만, 더 이상은 아니다. <<1>>은 그녀가 가름대 도적단에게 살해당했다고 "
"생각한다. \\\\"\\\\"스쿠마를 사용하는 자들의 일반적인 말로\\\\"\\\\"라고 했었지. 웃기는 소리! 내 아내는 스쿠마광이 아니었다. "
"그녀의 기억을 그따위로 모욕하다니!"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"그 카짓의 추측은 무시하고, 비난받을 자들은 가름대 놈들이다. 증거가 너무나도 명확하다. 그녀가 발견됐던 해안가 주변에는 깨진 유리병이 "
"흩어져 있었고, 그녀의 얼굴에 상처를 남겼단 말이다. 전부 밀수꾼들이 범인이라는 것을 가리킨다. 트리니막이시여 절 도우소서. 그녀의 "
"복수를 이룰 것이다!"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"항목 272"
"\n"
"일 주일의 대부분을 부두에서 기다리면서 보냈다. 그 악마들 중 한 놈이 거래를 하는 모습을 보았다. 놈을 따라가려 했지만, 놈이 날 "
"발견했다. 짧은 휘파람 두 번, 긴 휘파람 한 번으로 소리를 냈었다. 반드시 기억해야 한다. 놈의 친구 둘이 지붕에서 나에게 뛰어들었다. "
"날 피투성이가 되도록 때렸다. 날 부두에 던져 놓았다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"밀물이 내 상처에서 피를 씻어낼 때 깨어났다. 지금도 따끔거린다. 이 해충 놈들을 쫓으려면, 물론 해충이고 말고! 난 내 스스로를 "
"방어하는 방법을 배워야 한다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"<<2>>은 튼튼한 녀석이자 좋은 친구다. 그는 수 년간 무례한 취객과 깡패들을 다루면서 많은 것을 배웠으며, 전사의 품위를 지녔다. "
"내일 아는 것을 가르쳐 달라고 부탁할 것이다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"항목 273"
"\n"
"<<2>>은 웃음을 멈추질 못했다. 내가 단맛케이크를 조르는 아기고양이 같다고 했다! 내가 사정을 설명하고 날 가르쳐줄 수 있느냐고 "
"물어봤을 때, 그는 태도를 바꾸었다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"그는 이렇게 말했다. \\\\"\\\\"<<3>>  사원으로 가 보세요. <<4>>에게 부탁하시고요. 제게 말씀하신 것을 그대로 들려 주세요."
"\\\\"\\\\""
"\n"
""
"\n"
"내일 떠날 것이다. <<5>>에게는 <<6>> 근처 조수 웅덩이로 낚시를 간다고 말해 두었다. 그 애는 날 믿는 것 같다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"항목 274"
"\n"
"<<4>>의 이야기는 나와 다르지 않았다. 그녀는 가름대 놈들에게 오빠를 잃고 <<6>>으로 왔다고 했다. 그녀는 싸우는 법을 배우고 "
"싶어했다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"하지만 그녀는 수도승들이 생각하는 법을 훈련받는다고 했다. 모든 싸움 수련은 수수께끼였다. 학생들이 수수께끼를 이해하였음을 보여주기 "
"전까지는 진보할 수가 없었다. 리들'타르는 그녀에게 지시를 내려 주었고 복수의 필요성을 정의를 위한 갈망으로 조절해 주었다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"그녀가 행동을 보여 줬을 때, 그것은 계산적이었고 정확했다. 가름대 놈들은 그것이 우연이 아니었다는 사실을 결코 깨닫지 못했다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"항목 275"
"\n"
"내 수련은 잘 진행되고 있다. 리들'타르를 이해하는 것이 좀 어렵긴 하지만 말이다. 자기 자신을 더 거대한 도식의 아주 작은 부분으로 "
"바라보아야 하는 것 같다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"이전엔 볼 수 없었던 생각 방식이다. 옛 알드메리스에서의 방법과는 완전히 다르긴 하지만, 이쪽이 훨씬 더 융통성 있다는 것을 인정한다. "
"특히 도덕과 관련된 양심의 가책에 관해서 그렇다. 이것에 대해 명상해볼 것이다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"항목 276"
"\n"
"내 생각에 평온이 자리잡는다. 알아채기도 전에 잠이 쉽게 찾아온다. 꿈 속에서, 시리아렐의 실이 나의 실과 교차하는 곳에서, 우리 딸이 "
"날개를 펼치고 우리 모두를 가로막는 틀을 가로질러 날아오른다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"공허를 건너니, 가름대의 실이 밤중의 단검처럼 희미한 빛을 발한다. 저들의 끈을 잘라내는 것이 얼마나 쉬울 것인가! 저들을 어둠 너머로 "
"떨어뜨리는 것이 얼마나 쉬울 것인가!"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"하지만 불명확함은 최대의 적이다. 그러니 나는 기다린다. 나는 주시한다. 그리고 나는 배운다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"항목 277"
"\n"
"<<4>>가 말하길 가름대는 취약하다고 한다. 직접적인 대립은 무의미하다. 나머지와 떨어진 자들의 실을 잘라내고, 그 끈이 끊어질 때까지 "
"닳아 해어지도록 하는 것이 더 낫다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"이 카짓은 준비되었다."

#: 51188213-0-1607
msgctxt "51188213-0-1607"
msgid "Hinaamo's Journal"
msgstr "히나모의 일지"

#: 21337012-0-1554
msgctxt "21337012-0-1554"
msgid "I made the bargain. "
"\n"
"\nThe Special Blend is as popular as promised."
"\n"
"\nBusiness is booming, but at what cost? "
"\n"
"\nWhat have I done?"
msgstr "난 거래를 했다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"특별 블렌드는 약속대로 대인기다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"사업은 호황이지만, 그 대가는 뭘까?"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"내가 무슨 짓을 한 거지?"

#: 51188213-0-1554
msgctxt "51188213-0-1554"
msgid "Everfull Flagon Journal, Page 3"
msgstr "언제나 꽉찬 술집 일지, 3장"

#: 21337012-0-1553
msgctxt "21337012-0-1553"
msgid "An interesting fellow stopped by today. A mage of some sort, I think. Sat in a corner, kept his hood drawn over his features. At first, he was grim and kept to himself. After a mead, however, he asked about the village and my tavern. I confess, it felt good to unburden myself.The fellow listened sympathetically and indicated there might be a way to improve my situation. "
"\n"
"\nHe said he might know how to turn things around. To get customers in the door and make them stay for a while. He said he would return after he thought about the problem and consulted his books."
"\n"
"\nI can't wait to hear what he comes up with. I'd give anything to make this tavern successful."
msgstr ""
"오늘은 흥미로운 친구가 들렀다. 내 보기엔 무슨 마법사 같다. 구석에 앉아서 후드를 눌러쓰고 있었다. 처음에는 혼자 음침하게 있을 "
"뿐이었다. 하지만 벌꿀술을 마시고 나서는 마을과 내 술집에 대해 물어봤다. 고백하건대, 마치 스스로 짐을 내려놓은 기분이었다. 그 친구는 "
"동정하며 내 상황을 개선할 수도 있는 방법이 있음을 내비쳤다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"그는 상황을 반전시킬 방법을 알 지도 모른다고 했다. 손님들을 들여서 잠깐동안만 머물게 하라는 것이었다. 그는 문제에 대해 생각해 보고 "
"책을 찾아본 뒤에 돌아오겠다고 말했다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"그가 어떤 해답을 말해줄 것인지 기다릴 수가 없다. 이 술집을 성공시키기 위해서라면 무엇이라도 줄 것이다."

#: 51188213-0-1553
msgctxt "51188213-0-1553"
msgid "Everfull Flagon Journal, Page 2"
msgstr "언제나 꽉찬 술집 일지, 2장"

#: 21337012-0-1552
msgctxt "21337012-0-1552"
msgid "Business is dismal. Today I poured two mugs of mead. Just two. And one of the mugs was for me. "
"\n"
"\nWhy did I open a tavern in this tiny, lonely village? I thought that after a hard day's labor, people would want to drink and sing. But even the smith, who must work up a thirst, rarely comes in. "
"\n"
"\nI would pray for a miracle, but who would listen to the prayers of a simple tavern owner who's down on his luck?"
msgstr ""
"사업이 형편없다. 오늘은 벌꿀술을 두 잔 따랐다. 딱 두 잔. 그마저도 한 잔은 내가 마셨다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"내가 왜 이런 작고, 외딴 마을에다 술집을 열었을까? 난 하루의 고된 노동 후에는 사람들이 마시고 노래하길 원할 줄 알았다. 하지만 "
"분명히 목이 타는 일을 하는 대장장이마저도 거의 오지를 않는다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"기적을 바라며 기도할 수도 있겠지만, 누가 운수없는 단순한 술집 주인의 기도를 들어줄까?"

#: 51188213-0-1552
msgctxt "51188213-0-1552"
msgid "Everfull Flagon Journal, Page 1"
msgstr "언제나 꽉찬 술집 일지, 1장"

#: 21337012-0-1544
msgctxt "21337012-0-1544"
msgid "Captain,"
"\n"
"\nMartin continues to press us for details. I continue to tell him nothing. We're very deliberately staying out of the Bloodthorn's path. Whatever they have planned, we can't afford to be tarred by that brush."
"\n"
"\nMeanwhile, Lerineaux continues to work at the supply chain. We've identified a quartermaster in Wayrest with a drinking problem, and a Sentinel guard captain deep in gambling debts. We're certain we'll be able to start moving shipments across the borders soon."
"\n"
"\nStay in touch,"
"\n"
"\n— Kath of the Red Nails"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1544
msgctxt "51188213-0-1544"
msgid "Lerineaux's Concerns"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1345
msgctxt "21337012-0-1345"
msgid "22 Sun's Height"
"\n"
"\nGoing to be a good dig. I have a feeling. Sailed in without a hitch—Ferrand knows his business. We'll be rich and gone before the Orcs even know we're here."
"\n"
"\nIf they were smart they'd be digging in these ruins themselves. But I've never known Orcs to be particularly smart."
"\n"
"\n28 Sun's Height"
"\n"
"\nOne week with no loot. Atirr insists there's a room we haven't found, but I'm sick of listening to that Cat. It was a mistake to sign up for this dig. If the Orcs don't kill us, a cave-in will."
"\n"
"\n29 Sun's Height"
"\n"
"\nI can't believe it. The Cat found something! We discovered an old door hidden behind a bookcase. It hasn't been opened in Akatosh knows how long."
"\n"
"\nMight finally see a good score. Even one decent relic would be enough to make this trip worthwhile. We'll open it tomorrow, when Delphine gets back."
"\n"
"\n2 First Seed"
"\n"
"\nWhy did we do it? Why did we open that door? Did Attir know what would happen? I just can't get his screams out of my head."
"\n"
"\nNo relic is worth this. I'm leaving, no matter what Delphine says. Even if there is a curse, I didn't touch it. What would some long-dead Ayleid want with my soul, anyway?"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1345
msgctxt "51188213-0-1345"
msgid "Barjot's Journal"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1341
msgctxt "21337012-0-1341"
msgid "Hold back Jorunn's forces. I don't need much time."
"\n"
"\nSimply hold your positions. You have the advantage here. Jorunn and the so-called Pact have no choice but to make a frontal assault. We can hold them back indefinitely should they try."
"\n"
"\nBy the time Jorunn gets his army past the front line, I will be the rightful ruler of this land and Sovngarde itself will punish my brother. My redemption will become a legend beyond what Jorunn could ever have imagined, and those of you who fight here for me will be honored heroes."
"\n"
"\n— Fildgor, called Orcthane"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1341
msgctxt "51188213-0-1341"
msgid "Skuldafn Orders"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1322
msgctxt "21337012-0-1322"
msgid "Eldecil,"
"\n"
"\nBy no means is anyone to learn that the Veiled Heritance is here in Woodhearth until we are certain that Ayrenn is dead. You are to remain out of sight while our new recruit completes her mission. Your job is only to cover her escape in case she is pursued. If she were exposed, she would be of no more use to us than her sister was."
"\n"
"\nOnce you have assured her escape, you may rejoin the rest of our forces and resume preparations."
"\n"
"\n— Vicereeve Pelidil"
msgstr ""
"엘데실,"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"아이렌이 죽었다는 것이 확실해질 때까지는 여기 우드하스에 베일의 계승단이 있다는 걸 누구도 알아선 안 된다. 신입이 임무를 완수하는 동안 "
"너는 숨어 있어야 한다. 네 임무는 신입이 추격당할 때 그 녀석을 탈출시키는 것 뿐이다. 만약 신입이 노출된다면, 그 녀석의 자매가 "
"그랬듯이 더 이상 우리에게 쓸모가 없을 것이다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"신입이 확실하게 탈출한다면, 나머지 군대와 합류해서 준비를 재개하라."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"— 대리행정관 펠리딜"

#: 51188213-0-1322
msgctxt "51188213-0-1322"
msgid "Vicereeve Pelidil's Orders"
msgstr "대리행정관 펠리딜의 명령서"

#: 21337012-0-1295
msgctxt "21337012-0-1295"
msgid "Sergeant Kurlash,"
"\n"
"\nDo exactly as I say and tell no one. Take this crate of weapons to the dock northeast of Dro-Dara plantation. Leave it and return immediately. The pickup is not your concern."
"\n"
"\n— General Godrun"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1295
msgctxt "51188213-0-1295"
msgid "Kurlash's Orders"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1288
msgctxt "21337012-0-1288"
msgid "Moramat,"
"\n"
"\nHere's a chance to prove your usefulness. If any of Jorunn's forces slip through Ramorgal's net to the north or sneak out of the south gates, it is up to you to stop them."
"\n"
"\nAlso, I don't know what is going on over at that logging camp, but I do not want any surprises from that direction. Send a couple of your mages over there to see if we can use the situation to our advantage or to determine if it will cause us problems. Probably the best course is to leave well enough alone, but I leave that to you to decide."
"\n"
"\n— Fildgor"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1288
msgctxt "51188213-0-1288"
msgid "Shaman Moramat's Orders"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1287
msgctxt "21337012-0-1287"
msgid "Ramorgal,"
"\n"
"\nWe need to position ourselves around this encampment Jorunn has set up. Bitterblade's troops will protect the approach to Skuldafn and keep Jorunn's forces occupied."
"\n"
"\nYour job is to reinforce the other side of Jorunn's encampment. Keep them on edge and set up the potential to box them in. Start getting troops in place, out of range of any archers within the encampment. "
"\n"
"\nKeep an eye on the approach road as well. Let's make sure that no reinforcements can reach them."
"\n"
"\n— Fildgor"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1287
msgctxt "51188213-0-1287"
msgid "Spymaster Ramorgol's Orders"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1284
msgctxt "21337012-0-1284"
msgid "Lord Fildgor —"
"\n"
"\nWe've settled into Lost Knife, as directed. We just need to push these lazy miners to start producing a bit more ore. Probably have to set a few more examples to motivate them. The rotating hostage tactic is effective for keeping them in line with minimum bloodshed, but it doesn't necessarily make them more productive."
"\n"
"\nYou may want to send someone here to examine an unusual ore that we found. It has some odd properties, possibly magical in nature. It could prove useful. Or valuable. This is not my field of study, though. Send someone with more of a background in alchemy or metallurgy."
"\n"
"\n— Magister Osanne"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1284
msgctxt "51188213-0-1284"
msgid "Note from Magister Osanne"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1256
msgctxt "21337012-0-1256"
msgid "Recruit! You're only going to get one chance to get this right. Slip up and you're out!"
"\n"
"\n— Tell no one of the Veiled Keep, or our training grounds on the island. "
"\n"
"\n— Recognition phrases change every two days. Learn to memorize these phrases as if your life depended on them. It does."
"\n"
"\n— At all times, keep your gear in good order. Alandare in particular hates a sloppy uniform. Keep it clean. Keep your blade sharp."
"\n"
"\n— Try not to strut in front of the servile scum in Skywatch. Their day will come, but we must be patient."
msgstr ""
"신입! 네가 이 시험을 통과할 기회는 오직 한 번 뿐이다. 실수를 한다면 그대로 퇴출이다!"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"— 그 누구에게도 베일의 요새나 이 섬의 훈련장에 대해 말해선 안 된다."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"— 암구어는 이틀마다 바뀐다. 네 목숨이 달린 것처럼 암구어를 외워 두어라. 진짜로 목숨이 달렸으니까."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"— 언제나 네 장비를 잘 정돈해 두어라. 알란다레는 제복을 대충 입는 것을 특히 싫어한다. 제복을 깨끗하게 유지해라. 네 검도 날카롭게 "
"유지해라."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"— 스카이워치의 굴종적인 쓰레기들 앞에서 거들먹거리지 않도록 노력해라. 놈들을 처리할 날이 올 것이지만, 우리는 반드시 인내심을 가져야 "
"한다."

#: 51188213-0-1256
msgctxt "51188213-0-1256"
msgid "Welcome, Veiled Recruit"
msgstr "환영한다, 베일의 신입"

#: 21337012-0-1254
msgctxt "21337012-0-1254"
msgid "Kazok,"
"\n"
"\nAlthough your troops may be tempted to sneak into Windhelm during the Konunleikar, you need to restrain them. "
"\n"
"\nI don't care how you do it, but other plans are in place within the city. If I find out that you or your soldiers disrupted anything, it will mean your head!"
"\n"
"\n— Fildgor Orcthane"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1254
msgctxt "51188213-0-1254"
msgid "Warning from Fildgor"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1243
msgctxt "21337012-0-1243"
msgid "Use this instead of the shoulder knife. The dull shoulder knife they provide is useless against armor. This blade will cut through chain and plate. Use this blade when the fighting gets close, but don't let anyone get a good look at it."
"\n"
"\nWinning is important. I need to make it to the final competition."
"\n"
"\n— L"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1243
msgctxt "51188213-0-1243"
msgid "For the Preliminary Duels"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1242
msgctxt "21337012-0-1242"
msgid "Slip this poison into the kegs before your stint in the contest begins. The substance has no taste and its effects manifest fairly quickly. It will make the drinkers appear to have weak constitutions."
"\n"
"\nMake sure you consume the antidote before you start drinking and everything should work out fine."
"\n"
"\n— L"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1242
msgctxt "51188213-0-1242"
msgid "For the Drinking Contest"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1241
msgctxt "21337012-0-1241"
msgid "Set this incense upwind of the competition so that the faint smoke it creates flows toward them."
"\n"
"\nThe harshness of the smoke will sting their eyes and make it difficult to aim. Our competitor has special drops to protect her eyes and should be unaffected. In the end, another win for the Stormfist clan."
"\n"
"\n— L"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1241
msgctxt "51188213-0-1241"
msgid "For the Archery Competition"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1240
msgctxt "21337012-0-1240"
msgid "The tracker's competition requires an arrow doused with animal musk that is loosed into the woods. The competitors then attempt to track the arrow by watching the movements of animals attracted to the scent."
"\n"
"\nUse this bow to loose a noisemaker arrow with a string attached that follows the same path as the first arrow. The noise will spook the animals and make tracking them unreliable, but the string will lead our competitor to the prize."
"\n"
"\nThis is a difficult contest to manipulate, so we have our best tracker in the competition just to be safe."
"\n"
"\n— L"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1240
msgctxt "51188213-0-1240"
msgid "For the Tracker's Competition"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1211
msgctxt "21337012-0-1211"
msgid "You're costing us too much coin."
"\n"
"\nH. is getting tired of the expense of keeping all this cargo in a warehouse. Because you've also been somewhat less than discreet, we don't want you to stay in that hidden cave for much longer. To be honest, we don't think you're doing enough to keep that cave hidden."
"\n"
"\nClear out the cargo. Sell it. Quickly. We know how much its worth, so you can make up for your lackluster results by raising that money. We'll be keeping track of the profits. That way, we can both make a profit and get you out of there quicker."
"\n"
"\nH. is spending too much money on two things: the arena and you. If you can't do this properly, we could easily arrange for your men to end up in the arena."
"\n"
"\nWe'll be waiting to hear about the incredible profits you've amassed."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-1211
msgctxt "51188213-0-1211"
msgid "Farangel's Delve: Further Orders"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-1176
msgctxt "21337012-0-1176"
msgid "Orders for Tonight:"
"\n"
"\nThomic will be bringing in some eggs from the dreugh nests. Have the men take a few each and spread them around Dreughside. And quietly, mind! "
"\n"
"\nIf anyone sees you, throw them to the dreugh. And burn this letter after reading it—don't get any ideas about holding on to it to blackmail me later. "
"\n"
"\nI'll be upstairs in Arbogasque's house. The swine owes me rent."
"\n"
"\n— Baron Sorick"
msgstr ""
"오늘 밤에 해야 할 일:"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"Thomic이 드레우그 둥지에서 알 몇 개를 가지고 올 거다. 사람들에게 각각 나눠준 다음 Dreughside에 알을 뿌리도록 해. "
"조용히 말이야!"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"누가 너를 본다면, 그들을 드레우그에게 던져 버려. 그리고 이 편지는 읽고 난 다음 태워라. 이걸 가지고 나중에 나를 협박할 생각은 꿈도 "
"꾸지 마."
"\n"
""
"\n"
"ㅡ Sorick 남작"

#: 51188213-0-1176
msgctxt "51188213-0-1176"
msgid "Baron Sorick's Orders"
msgstr "Sorick 남작의 명령"

#: 21337012-0-1175
msgctxt "21337012-0-1175"
msgid "Slick Thomic, "
"\n"
"\nYou're my man with the lightest foot. Tonight, steal as many dreugh eggs as you can from their nests at the pools, and bring them back to the barracks house in Dreughside."
msgstr ""
"Slick Thomic,"
"\n"
""
"\n"
"너는 내 사람 중 발이 가장 가볍지. 오늘 밤, 웅덩이에 있는 드레우그 둥지에서 할 수 있는 한 알을 많이 훔쳐라. 그리고 알들을 "
"Dreughside에 있는 barracks house로 다시 가져 가."

#: 51188213-0-1175
msgctxt "51188213-0-1175"
msgid "Note in a Dead Man's Hand"
msgstr "죽은 남자의 손에 있는 쪽지"

#: 21337012-0-1045
msgctxt "21337012-0-1045"
msgid "Eislef suspects but doesn't know."
"\nNo telling what he'd do."
"\nRae found my pipe but didn't know. Told her it was one of Eislef's."
"\n"
"\nRunning low, might try moon sugar if I run out."
"\n"
"\nEvery time Eislef sees that Elf he yells at Rae."
"\nNot her fault. Can't help herself."
"\nI can't help her either."
"\n"
"\nSaw the Dunmer again. Eislef didn't."
"\nHad to warn him, make him go away."
"\nNo good can come of this, not the way Eislef feels."
msgstr ""

